"title": "7404: ordinances",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7404",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Specific acts of worship commanded by God, sometimes including the sacraments.</p>\n<h2>The ordinance of Passover and Unleavened Bread</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:14\">EXO 12:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:17\">EXO 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:24\">EXO 12:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:43\">EXO 12:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod13:10\">EXO 13:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:12\">NUM 9:12</a></p>\n<h2>The ordinance of the Day of Atonement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:34\">LEV 16:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:29\">LEV 16:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:31\">LEV 16:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:31\">LEV 23:31</a></p>\n<h2>The ordinance of the red-heifer ritual</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:2\">NUM 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:10\">NUM 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:21\">NUM 19:21</a></p>\n<h2>Other occasions of worship as ordinances</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:41\">LEV 23:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev24:3\">LEV 24:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num31:21\">NUM 31:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr2:4\">2CH 2:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:4\">PSA 81:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:14\">EZK 46:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ordinances associated with the priesthood</h2>\n<h3>The Aaronic priests</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:9\">EXO 29:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:43\">EXO 28:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:21\">EXO 30:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:36\">LEV 7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev10:9\">LEV 10:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:8\">NUM 10:8</a></p>\n<h3>The Levites</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:23\">NUM 18:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr8:14\">2CH 8:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ordinances in Christian worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:24-1Cor11:25\">1CO 11:24–11:25</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:26-Matt26:28\">MAT 26:26–26:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:22-Mark14:24\">MRK 14:22–14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:17-Luke22:20\">LUK 22:17–22:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:19–28:20</a> <em>Jesus Christ's commands to observe baptism and the Lord's Supper makes them ordinances of Christian worship</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:38\">ACT 2:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:15\">ACT 16:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:8\">ACT 18:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:16\">ACT 22:16</a></p>\n<h2>Ordinances were to be permanent</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:17\">LEV 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod27:21\">EXO 27:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:14\">LEV 23:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:21\">LEV 23:21</a></p>\n<h2>Ordinances were to be obeyed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:37\">2KI 17:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:25\">1SA 30:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:34\">2KI 17:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:10\">2CH 19:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr33:8\">2CH 33:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:24\">EZK 44:24</a></p>\n<h2>Ordinances were for Israelites and Gentiles alike</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num15:15\">NUM 15:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:14\">NUM 9:14</a></p>\n<h2>God's ordinances are of supreme value</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:9\">PSA 19:9</a></strong></p>",
